He spent his early childhood in Woodside, New York. After graduating as valedictorian of both the Bronx High School of Science and Columbia University, Yancopoulos received his MD and PhD degrees in 1987 from Columbia University’s College of Physicians & Surgeons. Following work in the field of molecular immunology at Columbia University with Dr. Fred Alt, for which he received the Lucille P. Markey Scholar Award,[2] he left academia in 1989 as a founding scientist for Regeneron Pharmaceuticals with Leonard Schleifer. Yancopoulos has been awarded Columbia University's Stevens Triennial Prize for Research and its University Medal of Excellence for Distinguished Achievement. He currently resides in Yorktown Heights[5]
